# Backend fetch conventions

- Use `fetch()` (native) for backend calls; do not add axios unless requested.
- Base URL is `http://127.0.0.1:8000` (do not hardcode any other host).
- Prefer typed helpers for consistency (e.g., `get<T>()`, `post<T>()`) and centralize request config.
- Handle non-2xx responses explicitly (check `res.ok`) and surface meaningful errors to the UI.
- Avoid caching bugs: pick appropriate `cache` / `next` options per endpoint (default to no-store for frequently changing dashboard data).
